  "text": "Regulation. The product of degS, whose promoter appears in clone 301, plays a regulatory role. This gene encodes a cytoplasmic membrane serine protease whose only known target is another inner membrane protein, RseA (3). RseA binds and represses E , a sigma factor associated with the bacterial response to envelope stress [CITATION_1] . When RseA is degraded by DegS, E is free to activate its regulon.",
